# WeatherMap UX Fixes + Dashboard Drag-Drop

**Created:** November 16, 2025
**Status:** 🟡 PLANNING
**Priority:** P1 - CRITICAL (User-reported bugs + missing feature)

---

## Overview

Fix critical UX issues in WeatherMap widget and implement drag-drop widget rearrangement directly on dashboard (not just in widget menu modal).

---

## Problem Statement

### Issue 1: WeatherMap Layout Problems
**User Feedback:** "The weather forecast + weather/map widget doesn't look great. The text box still extends off the widget, when you click the 5 day forecast option and then go back to the map it doesn't load."

**Current Problems:**
1. **Location input still overflows** - Despite previous fix, input extends beyond widget boundaries
2. **Map doesn't reload** - When switching from "5-Day Forecast" tab back to "Current" tab, map disappears/doesn't re-initialize
3. **Tabs instead of side-by-side** - User wants map AND forecast visible simultaneously, not tabbed UI

**Desired Behavior:**
- Map on left, forecast on right (side-by-side layout)
- WeatherMap widget defaults to 2x or 3x width
- No input overflow issues
- Map always visible (no tab switching)

### Issue 2: Dashboard Widget Reorganization
**User Feedback:** "I also cannot move widgets around outside of in the widget menu to reorder them. I should be able to reorganize, move around and resize without HAVING to go into the widgets menu."

**Current Behavior:**
- Can only resize via three-dot menu → size selector
- Can only reorder via widget menu modal → drag-drop list
- No direct manipulation on dashboard

**Desired Behavior:**
- Drag widgets directly on dashboard to reorder
- Resize widgets directly on dashboard (corner handles or similar)
- No need to open menu modals for basic layout adjustments

