## Proposed Changes

### Change 1: Fix WeatherMap Side-by-Side Layout

**File:** `src/widgets/WeatherMap.tsx`

**Remove Tabs, Add Side-by-Side:**
```tsx
<Widget id="weathermap" title="Weather & Location" headerAccessory={weatherStatsDisplay}>
  <div className="weathermap-widget flex gap-4 h-full">
    {/* Left: Map (60% width) */}
    <div className="map-section flex-[3] min-h-[320px]">
      <div ref={mapRef} className="w-full h-full rounded-xl overflow-hidden" />

      {/* Error overlay */}
      {error && <div className="error-banner">⚠️ {error}</div>}

      {/* GPS button */}
      <button onClick={getUserLocation} className="gps-button">📍</button>
    </div>

    {/* Right: 5-Day Forecast (40% width) */}
    <div className="forecast-section flex-[2] overflow-y-auto">
      <h3 className="text-sm font-semibold mb-3">5-Day Forecast</h3>
      {forecastLoading ? (
        <p>Loading...</p>
      ) : forecast.length > 0 ? (
        <div className="space-y-2">
          {forecast.map((day) => (
            <div key={day.date} className="forecast-day">
              <span>{formatDate(day.date)}</span>
              <span>{getWeatherIcon(day.weatherCode)}</span>
              <div>
                <div>High: {day.tempMax}°F</div>
                <div>Low: {day.tempMin}°F</div>
              </div>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      ) : (
        <p>No forecast data</p>
      )}
    </div>
  </div>
</Widget>
```

**Key Changes:**
- Remove `activeTab` state and tab buttons
- Use `flex` with `gap-4` for side-by-side layout
- Map: `flex-[3]` (60% width), Forecast: `flex-[2]` (40% width)
- Map always mounted (no conditional rendering)
- Auto-fetch forecast on mount (no tab switching needed)

**Responsive Behavior:**
- Desktop (>= 1024px): Side-by-side layout
- Tablet/Mobile (< 1024px): Stack vertically (map top, forecast bottom)

### Change 2: Set WeatherMap Default Size to 2x

**File:** `src/stores/useWidgetStore.ts`

**Update `enableWidget` to use widget-specific defaults:**
```typescript
enableWidget: (widgetId) => {
  set((state) => {
    if (!state.enabledWidgets.includes(widgetId)) {
      // Default sizes for specific widgets
      const defaultSize = widgetId === 'weathermap' ? 2 : 1;

      return {
        enabledWidgets: [...state.enabledWidgets, widgetId],
        widgetSizes: { ...state.widgetSizes, [widgetId]: state.widgetSizes[widgetId] || defaultSize },
      };
    }
    return state;
  });
},
```

**Alternative (Better):** Set initial size in `enabledWidgets` array init:
```typescript
enabledWidgets: [
  'tasksummary',
  'upcomingevents',
  'recentnotes',
  'quickadd',
  'quote',
  'crypto',
  'hackernews',
  'weathermap'
],
widgetSizes: {
  weathermap: 2, // Default to 2x width
},
```

### Change 3: Fix Location Input Overflow (Final Fix)

**File:** `src/widgets/WeatherMap.tsx`

**Issue:** Input extends beyond widget boundaries on narrow screens.

**Root Cause:** Input is in `headerAccessory` which has limited space.

**Solution:** Move location controls below header or inside map overlay:

**Option A:** Move to map overlay (recommended):
```tsx
{/* Inside map container */}
<div className="map-container relative">
  <div ref={mapRef} />

  {/* Location controls overlay - top-left */}
  <div className="absolute top-4 left-4 z-10 bg-white dark:bg-surface-dark-elevated rounded-lg shadow-lg p-2 max-w-[250px]">
    {showCityInput ? (
      <form onSubmit={handleCitySubmit} className="flex gap-2">
        <input
          value={cityInput}
          onChange={(e) => setCityInput(e.target.value)}
          placeholder="Enter city..."
          className="flex-1 min-w-0 px-2 py-1 text-xs..."
        />
        <button type="submit">Go</button>
        <button onClick={() => { setShowCityInput(false); getUserLocation(); }}>📍</button>
      </form>
    ) : (
      <button onClick={() => setShowCityInput(true)} className="text-xs">
        📍 {city || 'Set Location'} ✏️
      </button>
    )}
  </div>
</div>
```

**Option B:** Keep in header but fix overflow:
```tsx
<div className="flex items-center gap-2 max-w-[200px] min-w-0">
  <form className="flex gap-1 min-w-0 flex-1">
    <input className="flex-1 min-w-0 w-0 px-2 py-1 text-xs..." />
    <button>Go</button>
  </form>
</div>
```

**Recommendation:** Option A (map overlay) - cleaner separation, more space

### Change 4: Dashboard Drag-Drop Reordering

**File:** `src/pages/Dashboard.tsx`

**Current:**
```tsx
<Masonry>
  {enabledWidgets.map((widgetId) => (
    <div className="mb-6 ${sizeClass}">
      <Suspense fallback={<WidgetLoader />}>
        <WidgetComponent />
      </Suspense>
    </div>
  ))}
</Masonry>
```

**Proposed (with @dnd-kit):**
```tsx
import { DndContext, closestCenter, PointerSensor, useSensor, useSensors } from '@dnd-kit/core';
import { SortableContext, verticalListSortingStrategy, useSortable, arrayMove } from '@dnd-kit/sortable';
import { CSS } from '@dnd-kit/utilities';

// Sortable Widget Wrapper
const SortableWidget: React.FC<{ widgetId: string; sizeClass: string; children: React.ReactNode }> = ({
  widgetId,
  sizeClass,
  children,
}) => {
  const { attributes, listeners, setNodeRef, transform, transition, isDragging } = useSortable({
    id: widgetId,
  });

  const style = {
    transform: CSS.Transform.toString(transform),
    transition,
    opacity: isDragging ? 0.5 : 1,
  };

  return (
    <div ref={setNodeRef} style={style} className={`mb-6 ${sizeClass}`}>
      {/* Drag handle overlay (invisible but covers widget for dragging) */}
      <div {...attributes} {...listeners} className="absolute inset-0 cursor-move z-10 opacity-0 hover:opacity-100 hover:bg-accent-cyan/10" />
      {children}
    </div>
  );
};

// Dashboard render
const sensors = useSensors(
  useSensor(PointerSensor, {
    activationConstraint: { distance: 5 }, // Require 5px movement to start drag
  })
);

const handleDragEnd = (event: DragEndEvent) => {
  const { active, over } = event;
  if (over && active.id !== over.id) {
    const oldIndex = enabledWidgets.indexOf(active.id as string);
    const newIndex = enabledWidgets.indexOf(over.id as string);
    const newOrder = arrayMove(enabledWidgets, oldIndex, newIndex);
    reorderWidgets(newOrder);
  }
};

<DndContext sensors={sensors} collisionDetection={closestCenter} onDragEnd={handleDragEnd}>
  <SortableContext items={enabledWidgets} strategy={verticalListSortingStrategy}>
    <Masonry>
      {enabledWidgets.map((widgetId) => {
        const size = widgetSizes[widgetId] || 1;
        const sizeClass = size === 3 ? 'col-span-3' : size === 2 ? 'col-span-2' : '';
        const WidgetComponent = WIDGET_COMPONENTS[baseWidgetType];

        return (
          <SortableWidget key={widgetId} widgetId={widgetId} sizeClass={sizeClass}>
            <Suspense fallback={<WidgetLoader />}>
              <WidgetComponent />
            </Suspense>
          </SortableWidget>
        );
      })}
    </Masonry>
  </SortableContext>
</DndContext>
```

**Key Features:**
- Wrap each widget in `SortableWidget` component
- Drag handle overlays entire widget (cursor-move on hover)
- 5px activation distance (prevents accidental drags)
- Semi-transparent during drag (opacity: 0.5)
- Updates `enabledWidgets` order in store
- Masonry automatically repositions widgets

**Challenge:** Masonry vs Sortable
- Masonry dynamically positions widgets in columns
- @dnd-kit expects static positioning
- **Solution:** Use `verticalListSortingStrategy` (treats widgets as vertical list, ignores Masonry positioning)
- Masonry re-renders after order change, widgets settle into new positions

